{
  "texts": [
    "The key idea behind GCNs is to propagate and aggregate information from neighboring nodes to update the node representations.",
    "By considering the local neighborhood information of each node, GCNs capture both the node features and the relationships among nodes (Hell et al. 2020; Liang et al. 2021).",
    "Graph AutoEncoders (GAEs) are unsupervised learning frameworks used to learn low-dimensional representations of graph-structured data.",
    "The core idea behind GAEs is to encode the graph information into a compact representation and then reconstruct the original graph from this representation.",
    "In GAEs, a GCN is typically used as an encoder to transform the input graph into a latent representation."
  ]
}